						<summary>

						<p>On a slab bearing an image of Hanumān.</p>						

						<p>Vijayarāya [Dēvarāya II], 1441 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1363, Durmati, Kārtika śu. 11, Thursday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1441 A.D., October 26.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift by Pōtanāyiniṁgāru for the merit of his parents. The inscription is very much damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
